__Borki__ [ˈbɔrki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/Polish) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Mrozy, within Mińsk County, Masovian Voivodeship, in east-central Poland.[1]

The village has a population of 200.
